  "slug": "household-water-audit",
  "title": "Carrying out a household water audit",
  "subtitle": "Calculate daily per-person water use and identify the largest reduction opportunities",
  "excerpt": "The UK average is 142 litres per person per day. Toilets account for 30%, showers and baths 25%, and washing machines 15%. A household audit uses appliance ratings and usage counts to build a use-by-activity breakdown and identify whether toilet, shower, or garden use is the dominant saving opportunity.",
  "type": "TECHNIQUE",
  "sourceNotes": "Waterwise household water consumption data 2024. OFWAT annual water use per capita data. Water UK household usage breakdown.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Average UK water use is about 142 litres per person per day. Toilet uses 30 to 40 L, shower or bath 30 to 40 L, laundry 15 to 20 L, kitchen and drinking 10 to 15 L, and garden 5 to 40 L (very seasonal). This audit works out your real use by activity. It then shows what you could reach with better fittings.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Toilet",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Flush volume: single-flush old cistern 9-13 L; modern dual-flush 4-6 L; with a displacement device 7-11 L.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Average flushes per person per day: 5.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Daily use per person: old 9 L cistern × 5 = 45 L; modern 4 L × 5 = 20 L. Potential saving from retrofit: 25 L per person per day.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Shower",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Standard shower head: 12-15 L/min.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Low-flow shower head: 6-8 L/min.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "A 10-minute shower at 12 L/min = 120 L. At 6 L/min = 60 L.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Power showers (electric booster pumps) use 15-20 L/min, equivalent to a bath.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Laundry",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Modern A-rated washing machines: 40-60 L per wash cycle.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Older machines: 80-100 L per cycle.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Running full loads rather than half loads at the same cycle frequency halves laundry water use.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Leaks",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A dripping tap loses 15 L per day. A leaking toilet cistern (the fill valve running continuously) can lose 200-400 L per day, often silently. To check for a cistern leak, add a few drops of food colouring to the cistern water and do not flush. Check the toilet bowl after 15 minutes: colour present means the cistern is leaking past the flapper valve.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What 100 litres per day per person looks like",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "100 L/day per person is a commonly cited achievable target with efficient fittings and no behavioural change beyond switching to a low-flow shower head: 20 L toilet + 60 L shower (6 L/min for 10 min) + 20 L all other. Reducing shower time to 5 minutes drops this further to 70 L/day.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
